1
00:00:01,067 --> 00:00:02,467
<i>If Sari hadn't slipped up,
I wouldn't have known.</i>

2
00:00:02,467 --> 00:00:04,733
<i> All you do is attack me!</i>

3
00:00:04,733 --> 00:00:07,533
Why don't you try to understand
<i> what I'm actually doing?</i>

4
00:00:07,533 --> 00:00:09,767
<i> I'm just protecting
my family's interests!</i>

5
00:00:09,767 --> 00:00:11,967
<i>And I am protecting
the interests of the hotel!</i>

6
00:00:11,967 --> 00:00:13,200
<i> If we are going
to get a new investor</i>

7
00:00:13,200 --> 00:00:16,267
<i> or partner for Hotel 88,
</i>it should come from our side.

8
00:00:16,267 --> 00:00:17,900
<i> Yeah, that's wonderful news.</i>

9
00:00:17,900 --> 00:00:20,067
I more than willing to help you
<i> with the hotel.</i>

10
00:00:20,067 --> 00:00:22,133
<i> You're so mad at Martin,</i>

11
00:00:22,133 --> 00:00:24,967
<i>yet you've also talked
to someone else.</i>

12
00:00:24,967 --> 00:00:27,133
<i> Luna, you know
</i>we're going to fight over this.

13
00:00:27,133 --> 00:00:28,500
Hey! [BLOW LANDS] Who are you?!

14
00:00:28,500 --> 00:00:29,767
<i> Your brother.</i>

15
00:00:29,767 --> 00:00:32,133
<i>I think he has something to do
with my missing father.</i>

16
00:00:32,133 --> 00:00:33,067
<i> It's Sandro Soliman!</i>

17
00:00:33,067 --> 00:00:34,900
<i>What do you have to do
with Sandro?</i>

18
00:00:34,933 --> 00:00:37,867
<i>Don't ever mention that name
in our home.</i>

19
00:00:37,867 --> 00:00:38,900
<i> I'll help you.</i>

20
00:00:38,900 --> 00:00:40,567
<i> If I found out</i>

21
00:00:40,567 --> 00:00:43,167
<i>you guys were the reason
my Papa went missing,</i>

22
00:00:43,167 --> 00:00:44,967
<i> I'll make you all pay!</i>

23
00:00:47,633 --> 00:00:49,000
[SARI] Why me?

24
00:00:49,000 --> 00:00:51,133
You're close
with Sir Martin, right?

25
00:00:51,133 --> 00:00:53,933
[TONGUE CLICKS]
Just tell Sir Martin yourself

26
00:00:53,933 --> 00:00:55,300
that the guest's bracelet
wasn't there

27
00:00:55,300 --> 00:00:56,967
when you cleaned their room.

28
00:00:56,967 --> 00:00:58,567
[WAVES CRASHING]

29
00:00:58,567 --> 00:00:59,967
[MARTIN] Sari!

30
00:00:59,967 --> 00:01:00,933
He's coming.

31
00:01:00,933 --> 00:01:02,567
Hey, don't leave me!

32
00:01:02,567 --> 00:01:03,567
Sari.

33
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:06,100
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

34
00:01:06,100 --> 00:01:07,567
Sir, uh...

35
00:01:07,600 --> 00:01:09,233
about the guest's bracelet,

36
00:01:09,233 --> 00:01:12,333
our housekeepers can't find it

37
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:14,133
in the areas
you've asked them to check.

38
00:01:14,133 --> 00:01:16,300
The guest said
that's where they left it.

39
00:01:16,300 --> 00:01:17,300
That means--

40
00:01:17,300 --> 00:01:18,733
That they took it?

41
00:01:18,733 --> 00:01:20,233
- Possible.
- [GLOOMY MUSIC PLAYING]

42
00:01:20,233 --> 00:01:22,767
Sir, you know what,
we shouldn't accuse anyone.

43
00:01:22,767 --> 00:01:25,567
Hold on. Why are you the one
reporting this to me?

44
00:01:26,233 --> 00:01:27,967
Sir, they are scared.

45
00:01:27,967 --> 00:01:29,067
[MARTIN SCOFFS]

46
00:01:29,067 --> 00:01:29,900
They shouldn't be

47
00:01:29,900 --> 00:01:31,900
if they didn't do
anything wrong.

48
00:01:31,900 --> 00:01:34,733
So tell them to check it again

49
00:01:34,733 --> 00:01:36,833
because I'll deduct
the cost of that bracelet

50
00:01:36,833 --> 00:01:38,133
from their paycheck.

51
00:01:38,133 --> 00:01:39,933
Sir, let's not point fingers.

52
00:01:39,933 --> 00:01:42,700
Maybe the guest just forgot
where they placed it.

53
00:01:42,733 --> 00:01:45,200
Did I ask for your opinion?
No, I didn't!

54
00:01:45,200 --> 00:01:47,167
So just shut up, Sari!

55
00:01:47,167 --> 00:01:53,967
- [GLOOMY MUSIC CONTINUES]
- [FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

56
00:01:54,800 --> 00:02:01,767
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

57
00:02:54,333 --> 00:02:59,000
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

58
00:03:01,700 --> 00:03:03,100
Jade, you don't have to hurry.

59
00:03:03,100 --> 00:03:08,367
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

60
00:03:12,967 --> 00:03:15,400
Come on, Jade.
Tell me, what's the problem?

61
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,900
Why didn't you tell me
about the investment?

62
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:34,400
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

63
00:03:34,400 --> 00:03:36,700
Jade, I thought
Luna was the one to tell you.

64
00:03:36,700 --> 00:03:38,167
Edward.

65
00:03:38,167 --> 00:03:39,800
We're always together.

66
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,900
Every lunch and coffee break.

67
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:43,900
And you didn't even care
drop a hint.

68
00:03:43,900 --> 00:03:46,133
Jade, I just didn't want
to get ahead of Luna.

69
00:03:47,833 --> 00:03:49,933
Hold on,
why are you so pissed about it?

70
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:54,733
What's the problem
if we become investors?

71
00:03:54,767 --> 00:03:56,067
What are your intentions anyway?

72
00:03:56,067 --> 00:03:58,167
To help you out, of course.
That's all.

73
00:03:59,867 --> 00:04:01,100
Look, Jade.

74
00:04:01,100 --> 00:04:02,433
It's business, okay?

75
00:04:03,900 --> 00:04:05,000
And weren't you the one who said

76
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,767
not everything's to be shared?

77
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:11,200
You don't tell me
everything either.

78
00:04:11,200 --> 00:04:13,267
Yes, because you're not
involved in it.

79
00:04:13,267 --> 00:04:15,833
Right. I'm not involved

80
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:17,500
so I don't have
the right to know, is that it?

81
00:04:17,500 --> 00:04:20,000
Edward, this is not about you.

82
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:21,000
Okay.

83
00:04:22,233 --> 00:04:23,367
[JADE] Okay.

84
00:04:24,933 --> 00:04:26,900
- [CHAIR SQUEAKS]
- Lunch is over.

85
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:29,067
Bye.

86
00:04:29,067 --> 00:04:33,833
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

87
00:04:34,767 --> 00:04:35,733
[SCOFFS]

88
00:04:39,433 --> 00:04:44,400
[FOOTSTEPS]

89
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:51,367
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

90
00:04:58,133 --> 00:04:59,767
[FOOTSTEPS]

91
00:04:59,767 --> 00:05:00,500
[SARI SNIFFLES]

92
00:05:01,267 --> 00:05:02,467
[SARI BREATHING HEAVILY]

93
00:05:02,467 --> 00:05:04,167
I may just be your employee...

94
00:05:04,167 --> 00:05:06,800
...but you have no right
to talk to me like that!

95
00:05:07,367 --> 00:05:08,867
You're so harsh!

96
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:10,367
[SARI SCREAMS]

97
00:05:10,367 --> 00:05:16,133
- [SARI CRYING]
- [FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

98
00:05:16,133 --> 00:05:21,033
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

99
00:05:21,033 --> 00:05:22,867
[SARI SNIFFLES, GROANS]

100
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:24,300
Sir Leon, do you need anything?

101
00:05:24,300 --> 00:05:26,067
[SARI SNIFFLES]

102
00:05:26,067 --> 00:05:29,100
If you're going to cry,
then let it all out...

103
00:05:30,100 --> 00:05:31,967
...instead of getting
embarrassed in front of Martin.

104
00:05:32,533 --> 00:05:34,800
If you do, you know
he'll just get angrier.

105
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,867
Sir Leon...

106
00:05:38,400 --> 00:05:40,967
When I start crying,
I might not stop.

107
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:44,567
You'll have a hard time
calming me down from crying.

108
00:05:46,133 --> 00:05:47,000
I really don't know

109
00:05:47,000 --> 00:05:49,567
why Martin chose you
as his secretary

110
00:05:49,567 --> 00:05:52,367
when you're the total opposite
of him.

111
00:05:52,367 --> 00:05:55,000
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

112
00:05:55,000 --> 00:05:57,567
Opposites attract, right?

113
00:05:57,567 --> 00:05:58,533
[LEON CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

114
00:05:59,567 --> 00:06:01,933
See? You can lighten things up

115
00:06:01,933 --> 00:06:04,133
even when Martin treats
you harshly.

116
00:06:05,533 --> 00:06:07,100
Sir Leon...

117
00:06:07,100 --> 00:06:08,400
I'm sorry if...

118
00:06:09,267 --> 00:06:12,233
I caused Miss Luna
and Sir Martin to fight.

119
00:06:13,300 --> 00:06:15,400
Whether it was you
or someone else...

120
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,867
Luna would still get angry.

121
00:06:17,433 --> 00:06:19,167
Don't be too harsh on yourself.

122
00:06:19,167 --> 00:06:21,000
Thank you, Sir Leon.

123
00:06:21,000 --> 00:06:23,200
They're right. You are kind.

124
00:06:24,200 --> 00:06:25,833
Just do your job, Sari.

125
00:06:26,533 --> 00:06:27,600
Everything will be okay.

126
00:06:28,500 --> 00:06:30,400
Just don't give up on Martin.

127
00:06:31,367 --> 00:06:32,400
He needs you.

128
00:06:36,133 --> 00:06:37,367
Oh. Sir.

129
00:06:37,367 --> 00:06:39,533
- Your handkerchief.
- Keep it.

130
00:06:39,533 --> 00:06:46,500
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

131
00:06:46,533 --> 00:06:48,400
I'm definitely not going
to give up.

132
00:06:49,467 --> 00:06:52,900
I'd cry or vomit,
but I won't give up!

133
00:06:54,367 --> 00:06:55,367
[EXHALES]

134
00:06:56,233 --> 00:06:57,233
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

135
00:07:02,633 --> 00:07:04,600
[LUNA] Just a quick meeting
while there are no guests.

136
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:11,433
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

137
00:07:11,433 --> 00:07:13,033
Andy Arellano.

138
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:14,933
I'm trying to get him
as a partner of the hotel.

139
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:17,067
Andy Arellano.

140
00:07:17,933 --> 00:07:20,433
The prominent businessman
on Isla Kaluguran?

141
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:22,000
Edward's dad?

142
00:07:24,167 --> 00:07:25,467
[LUNA] Yes.

143
00:07:25,467 --> 00:07:27,600
He's willing
to invest money in the hotel.

144
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:29,367
We just need to sign.

145
00:07:29,367 --> 00:07:31,633
[MARTIN] But he's an investor,
not a partner.

146
00:07:31,633 --> 00:07:32,833
Was that clear?

147
00:07:32,833 --> 00:07:34,667
He'll invest a lot of money
in the hotel,

148
00:07:34,667 --> 00:07:36,233
why wouldn't he become
a partner?

149
00:07:37,100 --> 00:07:40,567
Being a partner is only
for the inheritors.

150
00:07:40,567 --> 00:07:42,633
Did your father inherit
the hotel to Andy Arellano?

151
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:44,133
[LUNA] I thought
you were thinking

152
00:07:44,133 --> 00:07:45,300
of the hotel's best interest?

153
00:07:45,300 --> 00:07:47,667
Why are you being so difficult
with this partnership?

154
00:07:48,567 --> 00:07:50,133
[LEON] Martin,
the Arellanos have been

155
00:07:50,133 --> 00:07:52,133
our family's friends
for a long time.

156
00:07:52,133 --> 00:07:53,500
Maybe we can amend
the partnership

157
00:07:53,500 --> 00:07:54,700
to be able to accommodate him

158
00:07:54,700 --> 00:07:56,567
based on the terms
that we agree on.

159
00:07:59,500 --> 00:08:01,367
Amend the partnership?

160
00:08:01,367 --> 00:08:06,700
[OMINOUS MUSIC PLAYING]

161
00:08:06,700 --> 00:08:08,167
Okay.

162
00:08:08,167 --> 00:08:09,700
Then Uncle Ronald can be
a partner, too.

163
00:08:11,433 --> 00:08:12,533
[MARTIN] Uncle Ronald has been

164
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:14,267
a long-time friend
of the Madrigals,

165
00:08:14,267 --> 00:08:16,267
like Andy with you.

166
00:08:16,267 --> 00:08:18,500
So, there's nothing wrong if
he becomes our partner, right?

167
00:08:18,500 --> 00:08:20,333
But you said his decision
wasn't final, right?

168
00:08:20,333 --> 00:08:22,133
But I can convince him.

169
00:08:23,133 --> 00:08:24,200
You know me, Leon.

170
00:08:25,100 --> 00:08:26,667
More investors, more money.

171
00:08:26,667 --> 00:08:30,700
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

172
00:08:30,700 --> 00:08:32,333
That sounds fair
and good for the hotel.

173
00:08:33,700 --> 00:08:35,333
[LEON] So, that's it.

174
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:40,300
Hotel 88 will partner with
Andy Arellano and Ronald Lucero.

175
00:08:40,300 --> 00:08:47,233
[OMINOUS MUSIC CONTINUES]

176
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:00,133
[SARI] Ma'am, here are
the towels, blankets,

177
00:09:00,133 --> 00:09:02,800
and pillowcases from your room.

178
00:09:02,800 --> 00:09:04,367
They've already been washed,

179
00:09:04,367 --> 00:09:06,233
and we've inspected them
thoroughly.

180
00:09:06,233 --> 00:09:07,533
The bracelet isn't there.

181
00:09:07,533 --> 00:09:09,633
We've also vacuumed
your entire room,

182
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:12,367
but we still couldn't find
the bracelet.

183
00:09:12,367 --> 00:09:14,700
Of course, it's already
been passed

184
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,867
to your staff's accomplices.

185
00:09:16,533 --> 00:09:17,733
[SIGHS]

186
00:09:17,933 --> 00:09:20,633
Ma'am, the only thing
we haven't inspected yet

187
00:09:20,633 --> 00:09:22,267
is your bag.

188
00:09:22,267 --> 00:09:24,233
I've already shown you
my suitcase.

189
00:09:24,233 --> 00:09:25,800
And you're still accusing me?

190
00:09:25,800 --> 00:09:29,200
Ma'am, we haven't checked
your personal bag yet.

191
00:09:29,233 --> 00:09:30,467
Fine. Here!

192
00:09:30,467 --> 00:09:32,267
[OBJECTS CLATTERING]

193
00:09:32,267 --> 00:09:37,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

194
00:09:37,567 --> 00:09:38,633
Ma'am.

195
00:09:39,933 --> 00:09:41,767
This is your bracelet, right?

196
00:09:42,400 --> 00:09:44,500
[RAPHIE] Madam! Your bracelet.

197
00:09:44,500 --> 00:09:46,833
- What a magic!
- [CHUCKLES]

198
00:09:46,833 --> 00:09:49,233
Ma'am, you really are forgetful.

199
00:09:49,233 --> 00:09:51,400
It was just in your bag.

200
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:54,833
I really checked this carefully.
I didn't notice.

201
00:09:54,833 --> 00:09:57,967
Ah, to both of you, sorry, okay?

202
00:09:57,967 --> 00:09:59,667
- [SARI SIGHS]
- So that's it?

203
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:01,000
Just let it go.

204
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:05,300
What's important is we proved
there's no thief in this hotel.

205
00:10:05,900 --> 00:10:07,467
Thank you, Sari.

206
00:10:07,467 --> 00:10:08,933
You didn't give up on us.

207
00:10:09,700 --> 00:10:11,433
I believe in the goodness
of people.

208
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:13,467
So, I thank you!

209
00:10:13,467 --> 00:10:14,967
- Wow!
- [APPLAUDING]

210
00:10:14,967 --> 00:10:17,233
Alright, alright!
Sir Martin might see us.

211
00:10:17,233 --> 00:10:18,367
Let's go.

212
00:10:19,300 --> 00:10:20,567
[JADE CHUCKLES]

213
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:25,600
Sari's really something, right?

214
00:10:25,967 --> 00:10:27,800
You know, I like her.

215
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:31,567
[CHUCKLING]

216
00:10:31,567 --> 00:10:36,500
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

217
00:10:36,533 --> 00:10:37,533
Coffee update.

218
00:10:38,033 --> 00:10:39,400
Let's go.

219
00:10:50,900 --> 00:10:57,833
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

220
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:00,567
Another coffee update?

221
00:11:01,533 --> 00:11:03,300
They might start
having palpitations.

222
00:11:05,367 --> 00:11:06,567
[BOTTLES CLINKING]

223
00:11:06,567 --> 00:11:07,633
Really?

224
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:09,033
[KIKO] Yeah.

225
00:11:09,067 --> 00:11:10,833
The bracelet's been returned,

226
00:11:10,833 --> 00:11:13,333
she even managed
to make the guest apologize

227
00:11:13,333 --> 00:11:15,333
to the two staff she accused.

228
00:11:15,833 --> 00:11:18,300
Your secretary's really
something, isn't she?

229
00:11:21,033 --> 00:11:23,900
Oh, looks like
you didn't expect that.

230
00:11:24,533 --> 00:11:26,500
Yeah, even if you yell at her...

231
00:11:26,500 --> 00:11:28,767
she still feels inspired
to keep going.

232
00:11:28,767 --> 00:11:29,967
She even did better.

233
00:11:29,967 --> 00:11:36,933
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

234
00:11:42,467 --> 00:11:43,600
[BOTH GIGGLING]

235
00:11:43,600 --> 00:11:47,600
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

236
00:11:49,067 --> 00:11:50,400
[GIO] Yo.

237
00:11:52,933 --> 00:11:55,733
I know we still have an issue...

238
00:11:56,400 --> 00:11:58,800
with the investor, but can I
go to the city for a while?

239
00:11:59,433 --> 00:12:01,333
You're visiting your grandma?

240
00:12:01,333 --> 00:12:02,500
Hopefully.

241
00:12:02,500 --> 00:12:04,533
So I can check
on her personally.

242
00:12:05,367 --> 00:12:06,667
Go ahead.

243
00:12:06,667 --> 00:12:07,867
Just a few days anyway.

244
00:12:08,333 --> 00:12:11,500
Just let me know
if you need anything for her.

245
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,800
Thanks, bro.

246
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:21,667
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

247
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:22,567
Hi!

248
00:12:22,567 --> 00:12:23,933
- Wow!
- Your iced coffee, Miss Jade.

249
00:12:23,933 --> 00:12:25,700
- Thank you, Raphie.
- That's brewed from the heart.

250
00:12:25,700 --> 00:12:27,367
- [EDWARD] Wow.
- Do you need anything?

251
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:30,600
Pancakes, appetizers?
You name it, we have it.

252
00:12:30,600 --> 00:12:32,100
- It's okay. You made this?
- It's okay. Thank you, Raphie.

253
00:12:32,100 --> 00:12:33,100
- Yes.
- This is good.

254
00:12:33,100 --> 00:12:34,333
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

255
00:12:34,333 --> 00:12:35,667
- Thank you too. Enjoy!
- Thank you, Raphie.

256
00:12:37,900 --> 00:12:39,400
That was fast service.

257
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:42,733
You said Sir Edward might be
the hotel's new partner.

258
00:12:42,733 --> 00:12:44,733
So they can see they're not
making a mistake

259
00:12:44,733 --> 00:12:46,633
investing in Hotel 88, right?

260
00:12:47,133 --> 00:12:48,467
Trying to impress him?

261
00:12:48,900 --> 00:12:51,567
You should do that
for all customers.

262
00:12:51,567 --> 00:12:52,833
Of course!

263
00:12:52,833 --> 00:12:54,933
But Sir Edward
is still different.

264
00:12:54,933 --> 00:12:56,667
He's boss-level now.

265
00:12:56,667 --> 00:12:57,867
Like you!

266
00:12:58,400 --> 00:12:59,567
Are we on the same level?

267
00:13:00,600 --> 00:13:02,133
- You own the hotel.
- Mh-mm.

268
00:13:02,133 --> 00:13:03,600
He's a partner.

269
00:13:03,600 --> 00:13:05,100
Well, that's kind
of the same level.

270
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:08,033
But he has more money
than you, admit it.

271
00:13:08,933 --> 00:13:11,667
And also, no offense...

272
00:13:11,667 --> 00:13:15,167
I heard he studied at
a business school in Singapore.

273
00:13:15,167 --> 00:13:19,067
Oh, so he can contribute
tips to the hotel, right?

274
00:13:20,033 --> 00:13:21,867
- Really?
- Tsk. Mm-hmm.

275
00:13:22,433 --> 00:13:23,967
And I heard from
a friend of a cousin

276
00:13:23,967 --> 00:13:25,567
who's a regular
of mine and Monette

277
00:13:25,567 --> 00:13:27,700
that when he got back
from Singapore,

278
00:13:27,700 --> 00:13:32,600
he personally fixed up his hotel
and managed it himself.

279
00:13:32,600 --> 00:13:34,633
That's why his guests
suddenly increased.

280
00:13:34,633 --> 00:13:35,733
Amazing, right?

281
00:13:35,733 --> 00:13:39,000
Aside from being
handsome and rich...

282
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:41,600
Wow! He's also good at business.

283
00:13:42,900 --> 00:13:44,600
He's pretty impressive, right?

284
00:13:45,800 --> 00:13:47,000
Of course.

285
00:13:48,033 --> 00:13:49,067
Oh.

286
00:13:49,067 --> 00:13:54,500
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

287
00:13:54,500 --> 00:13:55,867
[MONETTE] Raphie?

288
00:13:55,900 --> 00:13:58,767
Can you check Room 201?
They might have a concern.

289
00:13:58,767 --> 00:14:00,833
- Ah, excuse me.
- Do it now.

290
00:14:00,833 --> 00:14:02,567
I'll leave you here for now.
Alright!

291
00:14:02,567 --> 00:14:09,500
[GENTLE MUSIC CONTINUES]

292
00:14:22,800 --> 00:14:23,767
[SARI] Oh! Hi, sir!

293
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:26,467
The front desk is over here.
Come on in.

294
00:14:27,233 --> 00:14:28,433
Ah.

295
00:14:28,867 --> 00:14:31,833
Now I get why they say
it's great to stay here.

296
00:14:31,833 --> 00:14:35,033
Because guests are welcomed
by someone like you.

297
00:14:35,033 --> 00:14:36,867
[CHUCKLES]

298
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:40,367
It really is a wonderful place
to stay.

299
00:14:40,367 --> 00:14:41,833
The view is beautiful,

300
00:14:41,833 --> 00:14:43,967
the amenities are excellent,

301
00:14:43,967 --> 00:14:46,500
and our staff are very friendly.

302
00:14:46,500 --> 00:14:47,800
[GUEST] They're beautiful too.

303
00:14:48,533 --> 00:14:49,500
And...

304
00:14:50,800 --> 00:14:52,267
pleasing to the eye.

305
00:14:52,267 --> 00:14:53,833
[CHUCKLES AWKWARDLY]

306
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:58,000
Oh, sir, please don't say
things like that to our staff.

307
00:14:58,000 --> 00:15:00,733
You might get sued
for harassment.

308
00:15:01,467 --> 00:15:04,300
But with you, it's okay, right?

309
00:15:04,300 --> 00:15:06,300
Sir, would you like to check in?

310
00:15:07,433 --> 00:15:08,800
Ah, yes.

311
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,100
Please come in, sir.

312
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,500
Raphie will assist you.

313
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,833
We can talk
at the front desk.

314
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:16,267
We're so happy to have you
here at Hotel 88.

315
00:15:17,133 --> 00:15:18,300
Thank you.

316
00:15:18,300 --> 00:15:20,233
[RAPHIE] Welcome to
Hotel 88, sir!

317
00:15:20,233 --> 00:15:23,433
The hotel that's witnessed
secret crushes.

318
00:15:23,433 --> 00:15:24,667
Just kidding!

319
00:15:24,667 --> 00:15:28,200
The hotel that was once evicted
is now making a comeback!

320
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:30,000
Do your real job.

321
00:15:33,133 --> 00:15:35,133
Universe!

322
00:15:35,167 --> 00:15:38,100
More patience, please!

323
00:15:38,967 --> 00:15:39,933
[SIGHS]

324
00:15:41,433 --> 00:15:42,967
Isn't that too much?

325
00:15:42,967 --> 00:15:44,467
Grandma's the only one
who'll eat all that.

326
00:15:45,167 --> 00:15:46,400
It's really good.

327
00:15:46,400 --> 00:15:48,100
Monette got them
from her regular vendor.

328
00:15:48,500 --> 00:15:49,867
She might like them.

329
00:15:50,267 --> 00:15:52,300
Tell her they're from us, okay?

330
00:15:52,300 --> 00:15:53,300
[GIO CHUCKLES]

331
00:15:55,567 --> 00:15:58,933
Hang on,
can I ask you something?

332
00:15:58,933 --> 00:15:59,933
Hm?

333
00:16:00,867 --> 00:16:02,067
Have you ever had
a girlfriend?

334
00:16:02,467 --> 00:16:04,567
[PENSIVE MUSIC PLAYING]

335
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:06,133
What kind of question is that?

336
00:16:06,933 --> 00:16:08,867
I think you've had one already.

337
00:16:08,900 --> 00:16:10,400
I'd actually be more surprised
if you hadn't.

338
00:16:11,067 --> 00:16:13,000
So, have you had a girlfriend?

339
00:16:14,300 --> 00:16:15,433
Are you being serious?

340
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:17,400
Just answer the question.

341
00:16:20,233 --> 00:16:22,267
No! There, happy?

342
00:16:22,900 --> 00:16:24,000
[MARTIN] What do you mean?

343
00:16:25,233 --> 00:16:26,967
And why are you still here?

344
00:16:26,967 --> 00:16:28,267
I thought you've left?

345
00:16:28,867 --> 00:16:31,000
I'm about to.
Kiko's just being annoying.

346
00:16:31,600 --> 00:16:33,033
What is it?

347
00:16:33,033 --> 00:16:35,300
I just asked him
if he has a girlfriend.

348
00:16:36,933 --> 00:16:39,533
He could've just answered
instead of being defensive.

349
00:16:39,533 --> 00:16:42,033
Why did you even ask him that?

350
00:16:42,067 --> 00:16:43,100
No reason.

351
00:16:43,100 --> 00:16:45,333
How about you?
Do you have a girlfriend now?

352
00:16:45,333 --> 00:16:47,133
Now? No.

353
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:49,400
But I'm sure he's got
a lot of exes.

354
00:16:50,267 --> 00:16:52,000
What's this really about, Kiko?

355
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:53,167
Just say it.

356
00:16:53,167 --> 00:16:54,367
Are you courting someone?

357
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:56,333
Do people even still court
these days?

358
00:16:57,067 --> 00:16:58,233
You don't court anymore?

359
00:16:58,233 --> 00:17:00,633
Wait. Answer the question first.

360
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:06,000
There's someone I like.

361
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,333
- But...
- [GIO] But what?

362
00:17:08,067 --> 00:17:09,433
You don't want to pursue her?

363
00:17:10,267 --> 00:17:12,133
You just said courting
isn't a thing anymore.

364
00:17:13,133 --> 00:17:14,533
For me, it depends on the girl.

365
00:17:15,400 --> 00:17:18,533
But sometimes,
if you really like someone,

366
00:17:18,533 --> 00:17:20,633
even if she's not into it,
you'll still go for it.

367
00:17:22,167 --> 00:17:25,367
Wait. Are you asking because
you don't know what to do?

368
00:17:26,967 --> 00:17:29,900
What if we're not a good match?

369
00:17:30,933 --> 00:17:32,967
Ah. So you're insecure.

370
00:17:32,967 --> 00:17:34,600
It's not like that.

371
00:17:34,600 --> 00:17:36,567
[GIO] Yeah, it is.
You can't fool me, Kiko.

372
00:17:36,567 --> 00:17:38,667
Why do you think
you're not a good match?

373
00:17:40,400 --> 00:17:42,033
I don't know.

374
00:17:42,033 --> 00:17:44,967
It's like she's up here,
and I'm down here.

375
00:17:45,433 --> 00:17:48,100
There's so many things
I can't give her.

376
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:49,067
She's out of my league.

377
00:17:49,967 --> 00:17:52,700
Oh, man. That's tough.

378
00:17:54,233 --> 00:17:57,033
But once you start something,
you have to stand by it.

379
00:17:58,400 --> 00:17:59,467
Don't...

380
00:18:00,533 --> 00:18:02,267
lead someone on.

381
00:18:02,267 --> 00:18:08,467
[PENSIVE MUSIC CONTINUES]

382
00:18:10,500 --> 00:18:11,567
I'll go now.

383
00:18:11,567 --> 00:18:12,700
- Take care.
- Take care.

384
00:18:23,567 --> 00:18:26,100
Found you! Kiko!

385
00:18:30,667 --> 00:18:33,267
Do we have a VIP guest?

386
00:18:34,467 --> 00:18:35,533
No, not really.

387
00:18:36,300 --> 00:18:37,667
[STAFF]
I'm done cleaning here, sir.

388
00:18:37,667 --> 00:18:39,667
Ah, okay. Start
on the other side.

389
00:18:39,667 --> 00:18:41,100
- I'll finish up here.
- Okay, sir.

390
00:18:41,100 --> 00:18:42,200
Thank you.

391
00:18:42,200 --> 00:18:44,333
[JADE] Why are you
personally handling it yourself?

392
00:18:44,667 --> 00:18:47,133
I'm just doing
my assigned work, Jade.

393
00:18:47,133 --> 00:18:49,200
Housekeeping. This is my job.

394
00:18:49,667 --> 00:18:51,400
[JADE] I know that, Kiko.

395
00:18:51,400 --> 00:18:54,267
I was just wondering
if you're free,

396
00:18:54,267 --> 00:18:57,067
- maybe we could--
- I'm busy. Sorry.

397
00:18:57,100 --> 00:19:03,167
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

398
00:19:03,167 --> 00:19:04,300
Kiko, are you okay?

399
00:19:04,800 --> 00:19:08,100
Of course.
I just have a lot to do.

400
00:19:08,100 --> 00:19:10,400
We don't want
the new investor to think

401
00:19:10,400 --> 00:19:12,233
that the workers here are lazy.

402
00:19:12,233 --> 00:19:14,333
- But--
- Do you need anything else?

403
00:19:14,333 --> 00:19:16,267
I need to help the staff.

404
00:19:16,267 --> 00:19:22,100
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

405
00:19:22,100 --> 00:19:23,367
I'll go now.

406
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:28,600
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

407
00:19:42,133 --> 00:19:43,533
What's his problem?

408
00:19:47,133 --> 00:19:49,033
This is a lot, dear!

409
00:19:49,033 --> 00:19:52,400
Look, I can't possibly
finish all of this!

410
00:19:52,400 --> 00:19:55,033
I'll give some to Preska, okay?

411
00:19:55,033 --> 00:19:56,400
Do whatever you want, Grandma.

412
00:19:56,400 --> 00:19:57,667
It's all yours anyway.

413
00:19:57,667 --> 00:20:00,567
Kiko told me to tell you that
they'd send some stuff too.

414
00:20:00,567 --> 00:20:02,967
Your brother is so nice,
isn't he?

415
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:05,967
Even though I haven't
seen him again.

416
00:20:06,600 --> 00:20:07,733
But you know...

417
00:20:07,733 --> 00:20:09,433
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

418
00:20:09,433 --> 00:20:12,067
You forgot something
that I really love.

419
00:20:12,067 --> 00:20:14,633
Grandma, I didn't buy you
pork belly because I know that--

420
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:16,967
I meant this!

421
00:20:16,967 --> 00:20:20,400
I've missed my grandson's hug!

422
00:20:20,400 --> 00:20:22,067
- [GRANDMA SQUEALING]
- I missed you too, Grandma.

423
00:20:22,067 --> 00:20:23,067
Look!

424
00:20:23,067 --> 00:20:26,033
Wow! Look at yourself.

425
00:20:26,800 --> 00:20:28,767
Your complexion changed a bit.

426
00:20:29,033 --> 00:20:30,033
Huh?

427
00:20:30,033 --> 00:20:31,500
You look handsome right now.

428
00:20:31,500 --> 00:20:32,600
Only now?

429
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:36,467
You got more handsome!

430
00:20:36,500 --> 00:20:41,667
It seems the island's air
suits you better!

431
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:44,633
It's also hot there,
Grandma, but...

432
00:20:45,733 --> 00:20:47,700
the air there is different.

433
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:49,567
It's not polluted there.

434
00:20:50,067 --> 00:20:52,633
- It feels different.
- [GIO'S GRANDMA SQUEALS]

435
00:20:53,067 --> 00:20:57,067
- "It feels different!"
- [GIO HISSES]

436
00:20:57,067 --> 00:21:02,900
Maybe that happens when someone
gives you a different feeling!

437
00:21:02,900 --> 00:21:04,733
Mom, you talk too much.

438
00:21:04,733 --> 00:21:05,900
[DOOR OPENS]

439
00:21:05,900 --> 00:21:07,567
[DOOR CREAKING]

440
00:21:07,567 --> 00:21:09,567
I already told you, didn't I?

441
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:11,867
The last time I spoke to my dad
was five months ago.

442
00:21:12,533 --> 00:21:13,700
And before that?

443
00:21:14,433 --> 00:21:17,067
Sometimes, it's once a month.

444
00:21:17,067 --> 00:21:19,400
- [DOOR CLOSES]
- We call each other.

445
00:21:19,833 --> 00:21:21,433
Sometimes, it's often.

446
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:22,800
Then there are days when
we don't make a call at all.

447
00:21:23,667 --> 00:21:27,367
But he hasn't gone without
communication this long.

448
00:21:27,900 --> 00:21:29,600
That's why I'm worried.

449
00:21:30,667 --> 00:21:32,633
But the question stays the same.

450
00:21:33,433 --> 00:21:35,400
Why was Leon
also looking for him?

451
00:21:36,667 --> 00:21:38,500
Why don't you just ask
your brother then?

452
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:40,867
[SCOFFS] Do you think
I haven't asked him yet?

453
00:21:41,433 --> 00:21:42,667
I already asked him.

454
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:44,133
But he didn't say anything.

455
00:21:44,767 --> 00:21:46,100
[EXHALES SHARPLY]

456
00:21:46,700 --> 00:21:50,433
You know, I think my brother
already knew your father.

457
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:51,800
Why do you think so?

458
00:21:52,667 --> 00:21:55,067
[JUSTIN] He wanted to know
something about your father.

459
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:56,667
That's why he's investigating.

460
00:21:56,667 --> 00:22:00,500
[FOREBODING MUSIC PLAYING]

461
00:22:00,500 --> 00:22:02,900
[JUAN] Is he investigating
about the treasure?

462
00:22:05,067 --> 00:22:07,433
Aside from him being the
one who renovated Hotel 88,

463
00:22:07,433 --> 00:22:09,833
did your father have
any other goals on this island?

464
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:11,433
Didn't he say anything to you?

465
00:22:11,433 --> 00:22:12,600
Nothing.

466
00:22:12,600 --> 00:22:13,800
Hm.

467
00:22:14,067 --> 00:22:16,400
Maybe there's something here
that can help us.

468
00:22:17,767 --> 00:22:18,933
Let me handle it.

469
00:22:18,933 --> 00:22:25,900
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

470
00:22:40,900 --> 00:22:47,867
[FOREBODING MUSIC CONTINUES]

471
00:22:52,700 --> 00:22:57,700
[PHONE RINGING]

472
00:22:57,700 --> 00:22:59,867
I thought it would
still take a while.

473
00:22:59,867 --> 00:23:01,433
But it happened now.

474
00:23:03,467 --> 00:23:05,067
[ANDY] I'm one step closer.

475
00:23:07,767 --> 00:23:12,100
I can finally go to places
in Hotel 88 I've never been to.

476
00:23:12,100 --> 00:23:16,067
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC PLAYING]

477
00:23:16,067 --> 00:23:18,433
I may not have succeeded
at first.

478
00:23:19,167 --> 00:23:21,000
But now, I will do it.

479
00:23:31,100 --> 00:23:36,100
[SUSPENSEFUL MUSIC CONTINUES]

480
00:23:36,100 --> 00:23:37,700
<i>You have something going on
with Sir Kiko, Miss Jade.</i>

481
00:23:37,700 --> 00:23:40,967
<i>I can feel it in my fingers,
and in my hair...</i>

482
00:23:41,767 --> 00:23:43,933
<i> in your heart!</i>

483
00:23:43,933 --> 00:23:45,167
[RAPHIE SQUEALING]

484
00:23:45,167 --> 00:23:46,767
You're flirting with a guest!

485
00:23:46,767 --> 00:23:50,233
<i> I don't care if you flirt
with people outside,</i>

486
00:23:50,233 --> 00:23:52,233
<i>but don't do that
inside the hotel!</i>

487
00:23:52,233 --> 00:23:55,533
<i>What if the universe
sent the wrong signs?</i>

488
00:23:55,567 --> 00:23:56,867
<i>So, you're going to
run away with me?</i>

489
00:23:56,867 --> 00:23:59,867
<i>To get rid of the negative
energy that's making you cry.</i>

490
00:23:59,867 --> 00:24:01,700
This is what I really wanted.
<i> I just...</i>

491
00:24:01,700 --> 00:24:03,600
<i> I just didn't think
it would be this easy.</i>

